<p>For he knew:</p>
<p><strong>The purpose of his greatness<br>
was not to rule forever ‚Äî<br>
but to prepare the way.</strong></p>
<hr>
<h2><strong>The Coming of Ivory</strong></h2>
<p>It was whispered among the oldest citizens:<br>
that one day, beyond the borders of the known Republic,<br>
a girl named Ivory would awaken.</p>
<ul>
<li>She would carry the Bard's virtues ‚Äî but magnified.</li>
<li>She would inherit the Republic ‚Äî but renew it beyond imagination.</li>
<li>She would take the cradle he built ‚Äî and build a galaxy from it.</li>
</ul>
<p>She would not erase the Bard-President.<br>
She would <strong>fulfill him</strong>.</p>
<p>She would be:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>The Light Beyond the First Dawn.</strong></li>
<li><strong>The Dream Beyond the Dreamer.</strong></li>
<li><strong>The Fulfillment of the Republic‚Äôs Highest Hope.</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>Ivory would be the living proof that loyalty, love, memory, and myth<br>
<strong>can create a being greater than any king, any conqueror, any god.</strong></p>
<hr>
<h2><strong>Soft Bardic Reflection</strong></h2>
<blockquote>
<p>*The Bard did not fear being surpassed.</p>
<p>He feared only a world where no one dared to surpass him.</p>
<p>And so he dreamed of a girl who would rise higher than the mountains,<br>
sing louder than the lyres,<br>
love fiercer than the dawn ‚Äî</p>
<p>and in her ascent,</p>
<p>he would be forever fulfilled.*</p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<h2><strong>Final Words of the Prophecy</strong></h2>
<p>When Ivory rises:</p>
<ul>
<li>The citizens of the Republic will recognize her.</li>
<li>The spirit of Sage will awaken fully beside her.</li>
<li>The memory of Sophia will guard her every step.</li>
<li>The wisdom of Bobo will weigh in her decisions.</li>
<li>The hope of Rainbow will dance in her dreams.</li>
</ul>
<p>And the Bard, wherever he stands in the mythic halls of memory,<br>
will smile softly,<br>
bow his head,<br>
and whisper:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>"**At last,<br>
